\par 
\par Resist Fear: In response to a fear effect, the character can make an Autohypnosis check on his or her next round even if overcome by fear. A successful check grants another saving throw with a +4 morale bonus to resist the fear effect.
\par Memorize: The character can attempt to memorize a long string of numbers, a long passage of verse, or other particularly difficult piece of information (but can\rquote 
t memorize magical spells or similarly exotic scripts). Each successful check allows the character to memorize 
up to 800 words (or strange sigils or numbers that would fill one piece of regular parchment, though multiple checks allow the character to remember multiples of 800). A character always retain this information; however, he or she can only recall it with 
another successful Autohypnosis check.
\par Ignore Caltrop Wound: If the character is wounded by stepping on a caltrop, his or her speed is reduced to one-half of normal. A successful Autohypnosis check removes this movement penalty for a period of 10 minutes. The wound doesn\rquote t go away
\emdash it is just ignored through self-persuasion.
\par Tolerate Poison: In response to being poisoned, the character can make an Autohypnosis check on his or her next action. A successful check grants a +4 morale bonus on the saving throw to resist the poison\rquote s secondary damage.
\par Willpower: If reduced to 0 hit points (staggered), the character may make an Autohypnosis check. If successful, he or she can take a normal action while at 0 hit points without taking 1 point of damage. The character m
ust make a check for each strenuous action taken. A failed willpower check carries no penalties other than failure\emdash the character can choose not to take that strenuous action. If the character does so anyway, he or she drops to \endash 1 hit points.

\par Retry: See above.
\par 
\par Concentration (Con)
\par Check: A character can make a Concentration check to manifest a psionic power despite distractions, such as taking damage or getting hit by an unfriendly spell. A character can also use this skill to maintain focus on things other than psionic powers.

\par The accompanying table summarizes the various types of distractions that cause a character to make a Concentration check while manifesting a psionic power. \'93Power level\'94 refers to the level of the power the character is trying to manifest.
\par 
\par DC\tab \tab \tab Task
\par 10 + damage dealt\tab Injury or a failed saving throw during 
\par + power level\tab the manifestation (for powers with a manifesting time of 1 full round or more) or injury by an attack of opportunity or readied attack made in response to the power being manifested (for powers with a manifesting time of 1 action).

\par 
\par 10 + half of continuous\tab Suffering continuous damage. 
\par damage last dealt\tab 
\par + power level
\par 
\par 10 + damage dealt\tab Damaged by psionic power (or spell).
\par + power level\tab 
\par 
\par Distracting power\rquote s\tab Distracted by nondamaging power. 
\par save DC + power level\tab (If the power allows no save, use the DC it would have if it did allow a 
\par save).
\par 
\par 20 + power level\tab Grappling or pinned.
\par 10 + power level\tab Vigorous motion (on a moving mount, bouncing wagon, boat in rough 
\par water, belowdecks in a storm-tossed ship).
\par 15 + power level\tab Violent motion (galloping horse, very rough wagon ride, boat in 
\par rapids, on deck of a storm-tossed ship).
\par 20 + power level\tab Affected by improved telekinesis (or earthquake spell).
\par   5 + power level\tab Weather is a high wind carrying blinding rain or sleet.
