\par 15\tab \tab \tab Caster entangled by a net, snare, tanglefoot bag, or power or spell that 
\par similarly entangles the manifester.
\par Retry: Yes, though a success doesn\rquote t cancel the effects of a previous failure, which almost always is the loss of the power being manifested or the disruption of the power being concentrated on.
\par Special: A character with the Combat Manifestation feat gets a +4 bonus on Concentration checks made to manifest a power while on the defensive.
\par 
\par Knowledge (psionics)
\par (Int; Trained Only)
\par Like the Craft and Profession skills, Knowledge actually encompasses a number of unrelated skills, although this entry specifically relates to the body of lore dealing with the phenomena of psionics in all its many manifestations.
\par Check: Answering a question about psionics has a DC of 10 (for really easy questions), 15 (for basic questions), or 20 to 30 (for really tough questions). 
\par Retry: No. The check represents what a character knows, and thinking about a particular question regarding psionics a second time doesn\rquote t let a character know something he or she never learned in the first place.
\par Special: An untrained Knowledge (psionics) check is simply an Intelligence check. Without actual training, a character only knows common knowledge about psionics, which is often apocryphal.
\par If a character has 5 or more ranks of Autohypnosis, he or she gets a +2 synergy bonus on Knowledge (psionics) checks.
\par 
